; Purpose
; -------
; Alfred asked: "What can you build in a Scheme + Cortex + hosted-LLM
; stack that is genuinely interesting to real people — logic + reasoning
; + ML/AI + creative + systems — and IS ALSO the shape of good training
; data for Sakura's cognition?"
;
; This file answers that in seven sections:
;   1. What functional programming does well for logic + reasoning
;   2. What Cortex + hosted LLM adds
;   3. The 25 projects (curated table)
;   3.5. The two paired honest appendices for Book of CS Curriculum
;        (Drawbacks of Sakura Scheme + Where we did it better)
;   4. The prose shape (how these become CHAPTERS for two readers)
;   5. Cross-book placement matrix
;   6. Translation strategy
;
; CONTAINMENT RULE (Alfred, 2026-07-14, mid-flight amendment)
; -----------------------------------------------------------
; The advanced computer-science META-topics — functional vs imperative
; tradeoffs, writing imperatively in a functional language, implementing
; an imperative or declarative language IN Scheme, database internals,
; Hindley-Milner, the metacircular evaluator, paradigm comparison,
; compiler theory, complexity + amortized analysis + cache-oblivious
; algorithms, distributed systems fundamentals — are CONTAINED to Book
; of CS Curriculum by design. They do NOT scatter across the other 18
; books. Book of Motion teaches Scheme through motion; it does not have
; a 'functional vs imperative' chapter. Book of Music teaches Scheme
; through sound; it does not have a 'here's how to write imperative
; code in a functional language' section. Those meta-conversations
; live in one place. This earns engineer trust by not overloading every
; book with meta-analysis.
;
; Doctrine composed:
;   - project_books_teach_sakura_her_cognition_and_kid_scheme_2026_07_14
